The paper focuses on self-supervised representation learning for spatiotemporal features extracted from videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel method for training deep models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve action recognition, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
